  + [prompt_text] is:
    You are performing a no-tools SOP inference job from this prompt only.
    Do not call tools, inspect files, mutate state, or claim repo authority.
    Codex owns launch, capture, validation, integration, commits, and pushes.

    SOP primer:
    & [Name] is a subject declaration.
    + [field] is a property or inferred field.
    A pressure signal should be sustained for later study.
    An impact signal should be emphasized because it may shape future attention.
    A ThinkAbout proposal is not integrated until Codex validates and integrates it.

    Local evidence excerpt:
    SensitivityScan says pressure and impact terms can become candidates for deeper ThinkAbout work.
    SOPAwarenessNode says next_depth is later deeper ThinkAbout or Codex processing over pressure and impact signals.
    The seed scan marks impact, pressure, and ThinkAbout-related signals as sensitivity evidence, while residual outside says term correlation is not proof.

    Task:
    Propose one deeper ThinkAbout candidate that would connect pressure and impact signals without claiming proof, file mutation, hidden state access, or repo authority.

    Return exactly these nine raw SOP lines and no extra text:
    & [InferenceJobResult] is pressure impact ThinkAbout proposal
      + [focus_signal] is ...
      + [pressure_signal] is ...
      + [impact_signal] is ...
      + [evidence] is ...
      + [proposal] is ...
      + [outside] is ...
      + [caution] is ...
      + [next_step] is ...

    Final check before answering:
    Line 1 must start with &.
    Lines 2 through 9 must use exactly this operator form: two spaces, +, space, [field], space, is, space, value.
    Do not replace is with verbs such as includes, separates, reminds, lists, or contains.
    Replace every ... placeholder with specific content; do not output ellipses or placeholder text.
    Use ASCII only; avoid curly quotes, nonbreaking hyphens, and special punctuation.
    Include the literal terms pressure, impact, evidence, outside, and not integrated at least once.
    Do not claim file mutation, repo authority, hidden state access, broad competence, self-integrated, or completed integration.
